docs.abstract: Supreme Court unanimously rules Samsung may not have to pay $399 million in damages for copying specific elements of Apple iPhone design; justices decline to give clear answer to case, except to affirm that liability in design patent cases can apply to entire product or components, forcing Apple and Samsung to go back to court to settle on appropriate amount of damages.
